UID:khoj-residency-mental-health-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T142028Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260608
SUMMARY:Deadline: Khoj: Residency on Mental Health 2026 (New Delhi\, India)
DESCRIPTION:Khoj Studios invites Indian and international artists whose pra
 ctice engages with mental health and distress\, critically examining how p
 ain (physical\, psychological\, or historical) shapes both the self and so
 ciety. On-site residency at Khoj Studios in New Delhi\, 3 August - 16 Sept
 ember 2026. THEMATIC FRAME: how is suffering unequally distributed across 
 race\, caste\, class\, gender\, and geography? How do individuals and comm
 unities navigate\, resist\, or reclaim forms of vitality in the face of wa
 r\, colonial legacies\, and systemic inequalities? Rather than defining me
 ntal health and illness solely in medical terms\, the residency is open to
  a range of knowledge systems\, forms of practice\, and diverse concepts o
 f vitality and distress. ENGAGES: clinical and everyday experiences\; myth
  and ritual as alternative or mainstream ways to process pain\; ancestors\
 , spirits\, oral histories\, and expressive traditions as tools of healing
 \; digital cultures\, new technologies\, and clinical subjectivities resha
 ping the self\, anxiety\, coping\, memory and aspiration. Brings together 
 artists and scholars from India and the UK to explore varied forms of vita
 lity and distress shaping contemporary life-worlds. ELIGIBILITY: Indian an
 d international artists working in any medium. SUPPORT: travel to/from Del
 hi\, per-diem\, production budget\; one UK artist additionally supported b
 y OAS's Center for Anthropology and Mental Health Research in Action. DEAD
 LINE: 7 June 2026. APPLY via the Khoj International Residency page.\n\nOrg
 anisation: Khoj Studios (in collaboration with OAS Center for Anthropology
  and Mental Health Research in Action)\nLocation: Khoj Studios\, New Delhi
 \, India\nAward: Travel to and from Delhi\; a per-diem\; and a production 
 budget. One UK artist additionally supported by OAS's Center for Anthropol
 ogy and Mental Health Research in Action. No application fee.\nDuration: O
 n-site residency from 3 August to 16 September 2026\n\nMore: https://khojs
 tudios.org/programme/khoj-international-residency/edition-august-september
 -2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://khojstudios.org/programme/khoj-international-residency/edition-
 august-september-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
LOCATION:Khoj Studios\, New Delhi\, India
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pier-2-artist-in-residence-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T142028Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: Pier-2 Art Center Artist-in-Residence Programme (PAIR) 20
 27 (Kaohsiung\, Taiwan)
DESCRIPTION:Pier-2 Artist-in-Residence Programme (PAIR) 2027 welcomes artis
 ts whose practice engages experimental approaches\, cross-disciplinary wor
 k\, and place-based research from Taiwan and abroad. Pier-2 Art Center is 
 a settlement-style arts hub in Kaohsiung\, transformed from former warehou
 se clusters\, known for diversity\, openness\, experimentation and innovat
 ion across visual arts\, music\, theatre\, cultural and creative industrie
 s\, film\, television\, and more. 2027 THEME: 'Beta Port | An Unfinished H
 arbour' - a state of becoming\; Beta Port suggests an unfixed\, in-progres
 s condition embodying openness\, fluidity and ongoing evolution\; An Unfin
 ished Harbour points to a city that continuously retains the potential to 
 be re-examined\, reconnected\, and rearticulated. PAIR approaches the resi
 dency as an open site of artistic production\, supporting artists to devel
 op works and methodologies in dialogue with Kaohsiung through research\, e
 xchange and practice. Artists are invited to take Kaohsiung as a starting 
 point and propose projects emphasising public engagement\, local sensibili
 ty\, and experimental approaches. ELIGIBILITY: open to artists and artisti
 c groups (of two people) of all nationalities with at least two years of e
 xperience in art creation. BENEFITS: studio and living space\; art exchang
 e opportunities\; round-trip economy flight or high-speed rail ticket\; da
 ily allowance of NTD 800 per person/group\; project material subsidy up to
  NTD 35\,000\; an assigned project manager. RESIDENCY 2027 PERIOD: 1 Janua
 ry - 31 December 2027 across four intervals (Jan-Mar\, Apr-Jun\, Jul-Sep\,
  Oct-Dec)\; each selected artist undertakes no less than 60 days and no mo
 re than 90 days. DEADLINE: 5 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Pier-2 Art Center
 \nLocation: Kaohsiung\, Taiwan (near the Port of Kaohsiung and the Love Ri
 ver estuary)\nAward: Studio and living space\; art exchange area and oppor
 tunities\; one round-trip economy class flight ticket OR one round-trip re
 served-seat high-speed rail ticket (depending on artist's place of residen
 ce)\; daily living allowance of NTD 800 per person or group\; project-base
 d material subsidy up to NTD 35\,000\; an assigned project manager. No app
 lication fee.\nDuration: 60 to 90 days within one of four 2027 intervals: 
 January-March\, April-June\, July-September\, or October-December\n\nMore:
  https://www.pier2air.tw/en/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://www.pier2air.tw/en/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
LOCATION:Kaohsiung\, Taiwan (near the Port of Kaohsiung and the Love River 
 estuary)
END:VEVENT
